1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - This paper deals with the problem of fingerprint image recognition, which falls under the domain of computer vision.

3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Fingerprint recognition is a common application of multimedia technology, and this paper deals with the problem of missing pixels in fingerprint images. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Fingerprint recognition is often used as a biometric authentication technique in security systems, and this paper deals with the problem of reconstructing fingerprint images even when some pixels are missing. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The person identification task mentioned in this paper could potentially involve machine learning techniques for classification.
